chmod - command (SYMBOLIC METHOD) for permission ----->
SYNTAX => chmod option operator permission

DEFAULT PERMISSIONS =>   
DIRECTORY ---> OWNER  -rwx, 
               GROUP  -rx,
               PUBLIC -rx
FILE      ---> OWNER  -rw,
               GRPOUP  -r,
               PUBLIC -r
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
PERMISSION OPRETORS ->
ADD    =   '+'
remove =   '-'
set    =   '='
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OCTAL METHOD ->  SYNTAX => chmod no_for_user no_for_group n0_for_public file_name    (chmod 765 n1.txt)
rwx ->
0 - 000 - NO PERMISSION                              MODIFIED WAY => 1 EXECUTE
1 - 001 - EXECUTE                                                    2 WRITE
2 - 010 - WRITE                                                      4 READ      
3 - 011 - W&E
4 - 100 - READ
5 - 101 - READ & EXECUTE
6 - 110 - READ & WRITE
7 - 111 - READ, WRITE & EXECUTE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

